The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems and approximation algorithms, which are typically studied in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of valuations and selection heuristics also suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses experimental results and computational complexity, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the use of iterative algorithms and heuristics suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
